# Layout grammar

The registry ships four layout primitives. They are not interchangeable and
they are not "the same thing with different names". Use them correctly in
`ui/`, `components/`, and example blocks (including `examples/vite`).

## The four primitives

| Primitive | Renders | Direction | Role |
|-----------|---------|-----------|------|
| `Block`   | semantic landmark (`tag`) | ‚Äî | Opens every block exactly once per file. Carries the landmark `tag` (`aside`, `header`, `main`, `section`, `nav`, ‚Ä¶). |
| `Box`     | `<div>` (or other layout tag) | ‚Äî | Free-form inner container. Lives **only** inside `Block` (or another layout primitive). Never opens a block. |
| `Stack`   | `<div>` (vertical flex) | column | Vertical rhythm: sections, form fields, list rows. Base: `flex flex-col items-start justify-start`. |
| `Group`   | `<div>` or `<fieldset>` | row | Horizontal flex grouping. Base: `flex min-w-0`. Use `tag="fieldset"` for related form controls. |

## When to choose which

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Top of a file / start of any block | `Block` |
| Independent widget root that may live in its own file | `Block` (even when not a landmark ‚Äî default `<div>` is fine) |
| Inner container with no flex direction | `Box` |
| Stack rows top-to-bottom with consistent gap | `Stack` |
| Lay items in a row, wrap on small screens | `Group` |
| Group related form controls (`<fieldset>` semantics) | `Group tag="fieldset"` |
| Ordered/unordered list rendered as a stack | `Stack tag="ul"` (or `"ol"`) |
| Definition list rendered as a row | `Group tag="dl"` |

Rules of thumb:

- If you reach for `<div>`, ask first: would `Stack` or `Group` express intent?
  If neither rhythm nor row applies, use `Box`.
- A widget file does not need a landmark. `<Block>` (default `<div>`) is the
  correct root because every file has exactly one entry point ‚Äî that is what
  `Block` documents.
- Two `Box` in a row inside one `Block` is a smell ‚Äî usually `Stack` or `Group`
  was meant.

## Rules

1. **`Block` is the entry point of a block.** Each file or composite block
   begins with exactly one `Block`. Do not nest `Block` inside `Block` in the
   same file.
   - Exception: a child composite may own its own landmark `Block`
     (`Sidebar`, `Header`, etc.). The parent file must not re-wrap it with a
     duplicate landmark wrapper.
2. **`Box` is strictly inside `Block`.** `Box` never carries a landmark
   `tag` (`aside`, `header`, `main`, `section`, `nav`). Use `Block` for that.
3. **No raw markup in bricks or blocks.** Inside `ui/`, `components/`, and
   `examples/ui/blocks/`, do not write `<div>`, `<aside>`, `<section>`,
   `<header>`, etc. directly. Use `Block`/`Box`/`Stack`/`Group` (or another
   primitive/composite that wraps them).
   - Exception: brick root elements required by semantics (`<dialog>`,
     `<button>`, `<details>`, `<table>` family, `<form>`, `<fieldset>`).
  - Exception: `asChild` roots that intentionally delegate the semantic root to
    child markup (`<Card asChild><article>‚Ä¶</article></Card>`).
   - Exception: `examples/page.templ` and document shells (`<!DOCTYPE>`,
     `<html>`, `<head>`, `<body>`, asset tags).
4. **`Stack` is vertical.** Use it for top-to-bottom rhythm. Do not add
   `flex-row` overrides; if you need horizontal, switch to `Group`.
5. **`Group` is horizontal.** Use `tag="fieldset"` only when grouping related
   form controls; otherwise default `<div>`.
6. **`Block` appears at most once per file, and as the first JSX/templ node
   the file returns.** Subsequent containers inside that root use `Box`,
   `Stack`, or `Group`.

## Examples

Correct (block opens with `Block`, inner boxes use `Box`, vertical rhythm via
`Stack`, horizontal row via `Group`):

```templ
@ui.Block(ui.BlockProps{Tag: "aside", Class: "hidden w-64 md:flex md:flex-col"}) {
  @ui.Box(ui.BoxProps{Class: "flex h-16 items-center gap-4 border-b"}) {
    @cmp.IconBadge(cmp.IconBadgeProps{Size: "sm", Variant: "accent"}) { BY }
    @ui.Stack(ui.StackProps{Class: "gap-0"}) {
      @ui.Text(ui.TextProps{Class: "text-sm font-semibold"}) { Brand }
      @ui.Text(ui.TextProps{Class: "text-xs text-muted-foreground"}) { Subtitle }
    }
  }
}
```

Incorrect (raw markup, nested `Block`, wrong direction):

```templ
<aside class="hidden w-64 md:flex">            // raw markup ‚Äî forbidden
  @ui.Block(ui.BlockProps{Tag: "div"}) {        // Block inside Block ‚Äî forbidden
    @ui.Stack(ui.StackProps{Class: "flex-row"}) // Stack used for row ‚Äî use Group
      ‚Ä¶
    }
  }
}
```

## Validation

- `bun run lint:ui8px` scans `ui/`, `components/`, `utils/`, and `examples/`.
- `bash .validate/scripts/validate-spec.sh --with-tests` enforces spec contracts.
- `bun run typecheck:react` keeps the TSX side aligned.
- `go run ./.validate/cmd/blockonce` enforces rule 6 (one `<Block>` per file).
- A spec may declare `targets.react.test: <path>` (relative to the spec) ‚Äî the
  referenced TSX test file must exist on disk.

See [`templ-atomic-ui8px.mdc`](templ-atomic-ui8px.mdc) for the styling model
and [`templ-react-port.mdc`](templ-react-port.mdc) for the React port rules.
